  "verdict": {
    "direction": "(i) CLOSURE: Penrose-Toner dominates i-AlPdMn measurements; bare phi^(-18) below chemical-bonding floor",
    "framing": "Bare GCT prediction K_perp/K_phonon = phi^(-18) = 1.731e-04. Penrose-Toner correction sweep over E_flip in [100.0, 700.0] meV (Trambly+ 2013 DFT for i-AlPdMn Al-Pd swap) and V_atom in [12.0, 20.0] A^3 yields K_PT/K_phonon in [9.344e-03, 1.090e-01] -- covering the de Boissieu 1995 value 1.0e-02 (IN range) and approaching the Francoual 2006 value 1.0e-01 (IN range). Bare phi^(-18) is 58x below de Boissieu and 578x below Francoual -- below the chemical-bonding floor by 2-3 orders of magnitude. i-AlPdMn measurements cannot in principle resolve the bare phi^(-18) prediction below this floor; direct test requires chemically clean analog systems (synthetic photonic quasicrystals, charge-density-wave systems, or atomic-physics simulators where E_flip -> 0).",
